---
import Grid from "./Grid.astro";
import Icon from "./Icon.astro";
import cssUrl from "../styles/project-highlights.css?url";
---

<link rel="stylesheet" href={cssUrl} />

<section class="section with-background bg-variant project-highlights">
    <header class="section-header stack gap-1 lg:gap-2">
        <h3>Highlights</h3>
    </header>
    <div class="gallery">
        <Grid variant="small">
            <li class="project-card">
                <div class="project-title">
                    <span class="project-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                        <Icon icon="rocket-launch" size="1.2em" />
                    </span>
                    <h4>Platform Engineering Enablement</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="project-meta">
                    iptiQ (Swiss Re) · DevEx · DevOps · Leadership
                </p>
                <p>
                    Founded and led the company's Platform Engineering team,
                    focusing on DevEx and DevOps. Accelerated delivery and
                    reduced onboarding time while raising quality standards by
                    centralizing processes, tooling, and technology best
                    practices.
                </p>
            </li>

            <li class="project-card">
                <div class="project-title">
                    <span class="project-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                        <Icon icon="strategy" size="1.2em" />
                    </span>
                    <h4>AI-Powered Email Processing</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="project-meta">
                    iptiQ (Swiss Re) · AI Integration · AWS Bedrock
                </p>
                <p>
                    Integrated with AWS Bedrock to categorize incoming emails
                    from AWS SNS and trigger automated workflows. This first AI
                    integration reduced task execution time from ~7 minutes to
                    just ~15 seconds, delivering a step-change in efficiency.
                </p>
            </li>

            <li class="project-card">
                <div class="project-title">
                    <span class="project-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                        <Icon icon="trend_down" size="1.2em" color="green" />
                    </span>

                    <h4>Ephemeral Test Environments</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="project-meta">iptiQ (Swiss Re) · AWS · GitLab CI</p>
                <p>
                    Reduced E2E testing costs from ~€6,000 to ~€350/month and
                    cut cycle time from ~4h to ~40m by introducing automated,
                    on-demand ephemeral environments.
                </p>
            </li>

            <li class="project-card">
                <div class="project-title">
                    <span class="project-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                        <Icon icon="strategy" size="1.2em" />
                    </span>
                    <h4>AI MCP Integration Layer</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="project-meta">
                    iptiQ (Swiss Re) · AI Integration · AWS Bedrock · MCP ·
                    Analytics
                </p>
                <p>
                    Integrated MCPO (Model Context Protocol OpenAPI compatible)
                    into the platform, enabling natural language queries across
                    tools like Grafana, Prometheus, Elasticsearch, Jira, and
                    Confluence. This AI-powered integration allows quick
                    insights and multi-source data analysis without requiring
                    deep technical expertise.
                </p>
            </li>

            <li class="project-card">
                <div class="project-title">
                    <img
                        class="title-media"
                        src="/assets/kubernetes-ckad.avif"
                        alt="CKAD certification badge"
                        loading="lazy"
                        decoding="async"
                    />
                    <h4>CKAD — Certified Kubernetes Application Developer</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="project-meta">Linux Foundation / CNCF · Kubernetes</p>
                <p>
                    Certification focused on developing and deploying
                    applications in Kubernetes — covering pods, deployments,
                    configuration, observability, and troubleshooting in
                    real-world environments.
                </p>
            </li>

            <li class="project-card">
                <div class="project-title">
                    <span class="project-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                        <Icon icon="server" size="1.2em" />
                    </span>
                    <h4>OAuth2 Authentication Services</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="project-meta">
                    FinanceFair & iptiQ (Swiss Re) · Java · Spring Boot · OAuth2
                    · JWT
                </p>
                <p>
                    Implemented a standalone authentication microservice for a
                    distributed system, issuing and verifying JWT bearer tokens.
                    Centralized security across services with OAuth2 flows,
                    token validation, and standards-based integration.
                </p>
            </li>

            <li class="project-card">
                <div class="project-title">
                    <span class="project-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                        <Icon icon="code" size="1.2em" />
                    </span>
                    <h4>Distributed Core Platform</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="project-meta">
                    iptiQ (Swiss Re) · Java Spring Boot · Kafka · DDD/Hexagonal
                </p>
                <p>
                    Contributed to a scalable services platform using Kafka and
                    DDD/Hexagonal patterns to support insurance back-office
                    workloads.
                </p>
            </li>

            <!-- FinanceFair -->
            <li class="project-card">
                <div class="project-title">
                    <span class="project-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                        <Icon icon="code" size="1.2em" />
                    </span>
                    <h4>Double-Entry Accounting Engine</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="project-meta">
                    FinanceFair · Java Spring Boot · PostgreSQL · AWS
                </p>
                <p>
                    Designed and delivered a banking-grade ledger with strict
                    double-entry bookkeeping for financial operations.
                </p>
            </li>

            <li class="project-card">
                <div class="project-title">
                    <span class="project-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                        <Icon icon="list" size="1.2em" />
                    </span>
                    <h4>Auction & Trading System</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="project-meta">
                    FinanceFair · Java Spring Boot · Kafka
                </p>
                <p>
                    Built daily auctions for loan trading and bidding,
                    integrated with the platform’s core finance services.
                </p>
            </li>

            <li class="project-card">
                <div class="project-title">
                    <span class="project-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                        <Icon icon="server" size="1.2em" />
                    </span>
                    <h4>CI/CD & Cloud Migration</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="project-meta">
                    FinanceFair · Azure → AWS · GitHub Actions
                </p>
                <p>
                    Migrated platform to AWS and modernized CI/CD by replacing
                    Jenkins with GitHub Actions.
                </p>
            </li>

            <li class="project-card">
                <div class="project-title">
                    <span class="project-icon" aria-hidden="true">
                        <Icon icon="server" size="1.2em" />
                    </span>
                    <h4>Kafka Infrastructure</h4>
                </div>
                <p class="project-meta">arte · Apache Kafka</p>
                <p>
                    Delivered the company’s first Kafka infrastructure to
                    support streaming data pipelines across services.
                </p>
            </li>
        </Grid>
    </div>
</section>
